<p><b>Additional notes:</b>
</p>
<ul><li>If your question regards whether material constitutes <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research" title="Wikipedia:No original research">original research</a> or <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research#Synthesis_of_published_materia_that_advances_a_position" title="Wikipedia:No original research">original synthesis</a>, please use the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wikipedia:No_original_research/Noticeboard" title="Wikipedia:No original research/Noticeboard">no original research noticeboard</a> instead.</li>
<li>Discussion of fringe theories will depend entirely on their notability and reliable coverage in popular media. Above all, fringe theories should never be presented as fact.</li>
<li>Volunteers: To mark a discussion resolved, place <code>{{Resolved|Your reason here ~~~~}}</code> at the top of the section.</li></ul>
</td></tr>
